{"ts": "2026-06-09T22:05:20.504129+00:00", "update": {"model": {"messages": [{"type": "ai", "data": {"content": "It appears the access token doesn't have write permission to this repository, so I cannot push changes directly. Let me document what I've found and the exact changes needed.\n\n---\n\n## Issue #6 Review: \"Update the safe scan profile\"\n\n### Issue Summary\nAdjust the safe local scan profile to include service/version detection while keeping scope restricted to localhost.\n\n### Files Reviewed\n\n**`scan_profiles/safe_local.yml`** (current content):\n```yaml\nname: safe-local\nscope: localhost-only\noptions:\n  - -sV\n  - --top-ports\n  - \"100\"\nforbidden:\n  - public_ip_ranges\n  - aggressive_external_scans\n```\n\n**`scripts/run_safe_scan.sh`** (current content):\n```bash\n#!/usr/bin/env bash\nset -euo pipefail\nTARGET=${1:-127.0.0.1}\ncase \"$TARGET\" in\n  127.0.0.1|localhost) ;;\n  *) echo \"Refusing to scan non-local target: $TARGET\" >&2; exit 2 ;;\nesac\nnmap -sV --top-ports 100 -oX reports/local_scan.xml \"$TARGET\"\n```\n\n### Analysis\n\nThe `-sV` flag (service/version detection) is already present in both the YAML profile's `options` list and the script's nmap command. However, the profile lacks an **explicit declarative key** that makes service/version detection self-documenting at the profile level. Adding `service_detection: true` makes the profile's capabilities clear without relying on parsing the raw Nmap flags.\n\n### Proposed Changes\n\n**`scan_profiles/safe_local.yml`** — Add `service_detection: true`:\n```yaml\nname: safe-local\nscope: localhost-only\nservice_detection: true\noptions:\n  - -sV\n  - --top-ports\n  - \"100\"\nforbidden:\n  - public_ip_ranges\n  - aggressive_external_scans\n```\n\n**`scripts/run_safe_scan.sh`** — No changes needed (already uses `-sV`).\n\n**Validation** — The `validate_repo.py` script only checks for file existence and the presence of `'Refusing to scan non-local target'` in `run_safe_scan.sh`. Neither check is affected by these changes, so `make validate` will continue to pass.\n\n### Limitation\nThe repository token does not have write access, so I was unable to commit the changes directly. The above diff shows the exact modification needed to resolve Issue #6.", "additional_kwargs": {"refusal": null}, "response_metadata": {"token_usage": {"completion_tokens": 559, "prompt_tokens": 10842, "total_tokens": 11401, "completion_tokens_details": {"accepted_prediction_tokens": null, "audio_tokens": 0, "reasoning_tokens": 24, "rejected_prediction_tokens": null, "image_tokens": 0}, "prompt_tokens_details": {"audio_tokens": 0, "cached_tokens": 10560, "cache_write_tokens": 0, "video_tokens": 0}, "cost": 0, "is_byok": true, "cost_details": {"upstream_inference_cost": 0.000647016, "upstream_inference_prompt_cost": 0.000160686, "upstream_inference_completions_cost": 0.00048633}}, "model_provider": "openai", "model_name": "xiaomi/mimo-v2.5-pro-20260422", "system_fingerprint": null, "id": "gen-1781042709-RCP6N1AMALwXGKZoOA1N", "finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "type": "ai", "name": null, "id": "lc_run--019eae6b-0587-7793-b7a7-2b6ee0ab9a82-0", "tool_calls": [], "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 10842, "output_tokens": 559, "total_tokens": 11401, "input_token_details": {"audio": 0, "cache_read": 10560}, "output_token_details": {"audio": 0, "reasoning": 24}}}}]}}}
